    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2011 BMW M3 (E92), a pinnacle of naturally aspirated engineering featuring the S65 4.0L V8. This unit delivers a linear torque curve and a blistering 8,400 RPM redline, mated to a precise 6-speed longitudinal manual transmission. The chassis is equipped with Electronic Damping Control (EDC) and an M Variable Differential Lock, ensuring surgical turn-in and rear-axle stability. This example is mechanically flawless: preventative maintenance includes treated rod bearing replacement with ARP hardware and updated throttle actuators. The factory paint exhibits full depth with no swirl marks, and the undercarriage remains free of oxidation. Every bushing, seal, and heat shield is in showroom state, offering a tactile, analog driving experience that is increasingly rare.",
      "price": 48500.0,
